Description: Gold finger-ring; flat polygonal hoop of thin gold, broadening upwards; convex bezel; inscribed above and below in two lines, with a palm branch between the lines.
Bibliographic references: Finger Ring / Catalogue of the Finger Rings, Greek, Etruscan, and Roman, in the Departments of Antiquities, British Museum (615)
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Sir Augustus Wollaston Franks
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Rev Greville John Chester
